[[File:Basajaun.jpg|thumb|upright|Artist's depiction of a basajaun and his female companion, a basandere.]]
In [[Basque mythology]], '''Basajaun''' ("Lord of the Woods",<ref name=lurker/> plural: '''basajaunak''') is a huge, hairy hominid dwelling in the woods. They were thought to build [[megaliths]], protect [[Herd|flocks]] of livestock, and teach skills such as [[agriculture]] and [[ironworking]] to humans.

